<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="996" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="11.[812,1421,492,817]" pageId="11" pageNumber="996">
<emphasis box="[813,1420,492,516]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="996" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,971,492,516]" pageId="11" pageNumber="996">Identification.</emphasis>
Our specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1209,1352,492,516]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Platyvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="996" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachialis">
<emphasis box="[1209,1352,492,516]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="996">P. brachialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were
</emphasis>
identified based on the following combination of char- acters: posterior margin of male abdominal sternite 
<collectionCode box="[1391,1419,559,582]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="11" pageNumber="996">VI</collectionCode>
without projections; pronotum not shortened posteriorly, with anterior margin narrower than head width through eyes, and anterolateral angles not projected; and jugum, apex of pleurite VII, and base of VIII with several black denticles. Some of these features are not readily available from the literature but will be published in a forthcoming revision of the genus by 
<collectionCode box="[1075,1147,793,816]" pageId="11" pageNumber="996">FFFM</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
